# Example .envrc for direnv integration with nix-configs dev environments
#
# Copy this file to your project directory and rename to .envrc
# Then run: direnv allow
#
# Available dev shells:
#   vets-website      - Node 14.15.0, Yarn 1.x, Cypress
#   vets-api          - Ruby 3.3.6, PostgreSQL, Redis, Kafka
#   next-build        - Node 24, Yarn 3.x, Playwright
#   component-library - Node 22, Yarn 4.x, Puppeteer
#   content-build     - Node 14.15.0, Yarn 1.x, Cypress

# Option 1: Use absolute path (works from any directory)
use flake ~/code/nix-configs#vets-website

# Option 2: Use relative path (if nix-configs is a sibling directory)
# use flake ../nix-configs#vets-website

# Option 3: Use nix-direnv for faster shell activation (recommended)
# Requires nix-direnv to be installed (included in cli-tools module)
# use flake ~/code/nix-configs#vets-website --impure
